NOTE:PROFESSIONAL PROFILE\n\nEducation: BCom in Financial Accounting\, University of Cape Town (2016); MBA\, London Business School (2022-2024).\n\nScholarships and Awards: Laidlaw Foundation Women in Leadership Scholar; Forte Foundation Fellow.\n\nCareer History: Qualified Chartered Accountant with experience at Investec\, including roles as Investment Analyst and Fund Initiatives Consultant in private equity\, structured finance\, and corporate and institutional banking. Part of a five-person team that launched Africa's first renewable energy yieldco. Joined Alterra Capital Partners following completion of MBA.\n\nAreas of Expertise: Private equity; development finance; impact investing; renewable energy; sustainable development in Africa.\n\nSources:\nhttps://www.london.edu/masters-degrees/student-alumni-and-ambassadors/nhlanzeko-khanyile\nhttps://laidlawscholars.network/posts/scholar-spotlight-nhlanzeko-khanyile\nhttps://poetsandquants.com/2022/10/07/meet-the-mba-class-of-2024-nhlanzeko-khanyile-london-business-school/
